[§226-108]  Sustainability.  Priority
guidelines and principles to promote sustainability shall include:

     (1)  Encouraging balanced economic, social, community,
and environmental priorities;

     (2)  Encouraging planning that respects and promotes
living within the natural resources and limits of the State;

     (3)  Promoting a diversified and dynamic economy;

     (4)  Encouraging respect for the host culture;

     (5)  Promoting decisions based on meeting the needs of
the present without compromising the needs of future generations;

     (6)  Considering the principles of the ahupuaa system;
and

     (7)  Emphasizing that everyone, including individuals,
families, communities, businesses, and government, has the responsibility for
achieving a sustainable Hawaii. [L 2011, c 181, §2]

